The paper discusses the construction of decentralized data markets, which involves distributed data structures and incentivization mechanisms. This makes it likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for machine learning and AI, which suggests it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses security and trust issues, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
